<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="@System.Globalization.CultureInfo.CurrentUICulture.TwoLetterISOLanguageName"
      dir="@(CatDb.AdminUi.Resources.SupportedCultures.IsRightToLeft(System.Globalization.CultureInfo.CurrentUICulture) ? "rtl" : "ltr")">

<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <base href="/" />
    <ResourcePreloader />
    @* Applies the saved/OS-preferred theme before first paint (no flash of the wrong theme), and
       follows the OS setting live for as long as the user hasn't explicitly picked a theme via
       ThemeToggle (which stores an explicit 'catdb-theme' override and stops auto-following).
       This only covers the very first real document load, though: MainLayout's auth-redirect to
       /login (a client-side NavigateTo, no real reload) was observed wiping this class with no
       DOM mutation or "enhancedload" event visible to explain it — same story for the dir="rtl"/
       "ltr" attribute above right after a culture switch (a request-localization/streaming-render
       timing race). LayoutInitializer.razor (mounted in both layouts) is what actually re-applies
       both after that kind of in-app navigation; the "enhancedload" listener here is defense-in-
       depth for the same class of problem via a different navigation path (real enhanced-nav link
       clicks), not the primary fix. *@
    <script>
        (function () {
            var media = window.matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme: dark)');
            var apply = function () {
                var stored = localStorage.getItem('catdb-theme');
                var dark = stored ? stored === 'dark' : media.matches;
                document.documentElement.classList.toggle('dark', dark);
            };
            apply();
            media.addEventListener('change', function () {
                if (!localStorage.getItem('catdb-theme')) apply();
            });
            document.addEventListener('enhancedload', apply);
        })();
    </script>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="@Assets["app.css"]" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="@Assets["CatDb.AdminUi.styles.css"]" />
    <ImportMap />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="images/catdb-logo.svg" />
    <HeadOutlet />
</head>

<body class="bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-950">
    @* prerender:false — auth here is a scoped, circuit-only AuthenticationStateProvider (Basic-auth
       credentials, no ASP.NET Core Identity/cookie scheme). Prerendering would run the static SSR
       HTTP pass through the endpoint routing AuthorizationMiddleware before any circuit/auth-state
       exists, which then tries to ChallengeAsync() with no IAuthenticationService registered. *@
    <Routes @rendermode="new InteractiveServerRenderMode(prerender: false)" />
    <ReconnectModal />
    <script src="@Assets["_framework/blazor.web.js"]"></script>
</body>

</html>
